Plan for the smoke hardening (focused on low-flake, fast checks):

1. Create [`tests/e2e/smoke.spec.ts`] with stable selectors/assertions only.
2. Cover unauthenticated behavior first:
- `/dashboard` and `/nasabah` must redirect to `/login`.
- dokumen routes (`/dokumen/kuitansi/[id]`, `/dokumen/kartu-angsuran/[id]`, `/dokumen/pencairan/[id]`) must also gate behind login.
3. Add authenticated checks with one shared login helper:
- login page render consistency (title/form controls/demo text/link visibility).
- login success redirects to dashboard.
- `/dashboard` and `/nasabah` accessible after login.
- nasabah list page shows key table shell/heading without overfitting dynamic row content.
- dokumen routes are reachable in authenticated context (allow `200` or `404`, reject auth redirect and server crash patterns).
4. Add [`playwright.config.ts`] only with minimal defaults (`testDir`, `baseURL`, conservative timeouts/retries, single-project chromium) to keep smoke stable.
5. Run `npx playwright test tests/e2e/smoke.spec.ts` if environment permits, then commit only owned files.
